§ 195. There are various modes by which a freedwoman may have the other kinds of guardian: for instance, on manumission by a woman, when she must request a guardian under the lex Atilia, or in the provinces under the lex Julia and Titia, as a female patron cannot be guardian to a freedman or freedwoman: also on manumis- sion by a male, if with his sanction she makes a coemption, and then is remancipated and manumitted, for the patron then ceases to be guardian, and is replaced by the second manumitter, who is called a fiduciary guardian.
